<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-05-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-05-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="72" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d72">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">862.51/2879</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                    <gloss type="to">J. P. Morgan &amp; Co.</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-05-22">May 22, 1930</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sirs</hi>: The receipt is acknowledged of your
                            letter of May 21, 1930, regarding the contemplated issue of bonds of the
                            German Government.</p>
                        <p>The Department does not desire to interpose objection to the proposed
                            financing.</p>
                        <p>Very truly yours,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">H. L. Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>